In .NET 10, Android defaults to **edge-to-edge** rendering, which makes `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` ineffective. The window no longer physically resizes for the keyboard — instead you need to react to **IME (keyboard) insets**.

**Simplest fix — use `AdjustPan`:**

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(..., WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustPan)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

This pans the screen so the focused `Entry`/`Editor` stays visible. It works but may hide upper content.

---

**Better fix for a chat UI — respond to keyboard insets:**

Add padding to your input bar when the keyboard appears. In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Platform.Compatibility;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new InsetsListener());
}

private class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Bottom padding = keyboard height (minus nav bar already accounted for)
        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom - navInsets.Bottom, 0);

        if (v.RootView is View root)
            root.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

        return ViewCompat.OnApplyWindowInsets(v, insets);
    }
}
```

Then in your XAML, structure the chat screen normally:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Editor HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" AutoSize="TextChanges" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

---

**TL;DR:** `Resize` is dead on edge-to-edge Android. Use `AdjustPan` for a quick fix, or listen to IME insets for precise control over your chat input bar's position.
